President Muhammadu Buhari on Wednesday hosted several monarchs from the South West region of Nigeria at the State House, Abuja. Tolu Ogunlesi, who oversees the digital communications of the Presidency, on his verified Twitter handle revealed that the agenda of the meeting was security. He said that the delegation of South West monarchs was led by the Ooni of Ife, Oba Enitan Ogunwusi. Also present at the meeting were Vice President Yemi Osinbajo, and the Inspector General of Police, Mohammed Adamu. 